  "prompt": "How do I get a bar graph on Excel to sort from highest to lowest?",
  "response": "To sort a bar graph in Excel from highest to lowest, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Prepare Your Data**:\n   - Ensure your data is organized in a table format with labels in the first row and corresponding values below.\n   - Example:\n     ```\n     Category   Value\n     A          150\n     B          250\n     C          100\n     ```\n\n2. **Sort the Data**:\n   - Select the range of your data (including headers).\n   - Go to the **Data** tab in the Excel ribbon.\n   - Click on **Sort**.\n   - In the Sort dialog box, choose the column with the values (e.g., \"Value\").\n   - Select **Largest to Smallest** (or **Descending** depending on your version of Excel).\n   - Click **OK** to sort the data.\n\n3. **Create the Bar Graph**:\n   - Highlight the sorted data.\n   - Go to the **Insert** tab in the Excel ribbon.\n   - Choose a bar chart type (e.g., **Clustered Bar Chart**).\n\n4. **Verify the Order**:\n   - The bar chart should now display the categories from highest to lowest based on the sorted data.\n\nBy sorting the data before creating the chart, the bars will automatically appear in descending order. If you need to adjust the order after creating the chart, you can re-sort the data and the chart will update accordingly.",
